HEADWORD: Parthenon
<hw>Par"the*non</hw> <pr>(p⟦aum⟧r"th⟦esl⟧*n⟦ocr⟧n)</pr>, <pos>prop.
n.</pos> <ety>[L., fr. Gr. <grk>Parqenw`n</grk>, fr.<grk>parqe`nos</grk>
a virgin, i. e., Athena, the Greek goddess called also Pallas.]</ety>
<def>A celebrated marble temple of <persfn>Athena</persfn>, on the
Acropolis at <city>Athens</city>. It was of the pure Doric order, and
has had an important influence on art.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

